replies.body:
I was hoping someone would ask :).
Now I am by no means an expert on ap shen... or anything else for that matter but personally I find that ludens echo rush works really well. The move speed means that you can more easily walk up, throw a q and then walk back without taking to much harass. After ludens I normally go for lich bane to raise my burst with my passive up, a taunt into an auto attack into a Q does a surprising amount of damage. Rylais is pretty good on him because of how easy it is to just run after he burns taunt but I don't know how I feel about liandries, I play Shen for his burst and buying a liandries feels counter intuitive even if I have the rylais. Definatly pick up a rabadons and a zhonyas at some point, if you are agianst an AD mid I would recommend going zhonyas first but it only because 100% crucial during team fights when you can get a big taunt then zhonyas the burst they throw at you afterwards. As for boots lucidity work well because his cool-downs don't really favor those of a caster so they have pretty long cooldowns but I have made pen boots work also. If you do end up playing ap shen feel free to build anything else that makes sense, you are playing ap shen afterall... why stick to conformity now.

{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
